==English==

===Etymology===
Old English [[leof|lēof]], from Germanic ''*leubo-'', whence Gothic {{term|𐌻𐌹𐌿𐌱𐍃|sc=Goth|tr=liubs}}. Cognate with Dutch [[#Dutch|lief]], German [[lieb]], Russian {{term|любовь|tr=ljubóv’|lang=ru}}, Swedish and Norwegian Nynorsk [[ljuv]].

Adverb: Compare German ''[[lieber]]'', Dutch ''[[liever]]'', [[preferably]], [[rather]]

